\p{Let #{\TT \equiv\prn{\T,\eta,\mu}} be a monad on a category \C and let \I be an invertible [\em{weak} algebra](jms-00C8) for \TT; let \X be an arbitrary #{\TT}-algebra equipped with an endomap #{\Mor{\x}{\X}{\X}\in\C}. Then a homomorphism \Mor{j}{\I}{x\cdot\X} also tracks a homomorphism \Mor{j}{\ToMonadAlg{\I}}{\X}, where \ToMonadAlg{\I} is the [induced monad algebra](jms-00CD) of \I and #{\x\cdot\X} is the [restriction](jms-00CQ) of \X along \x.}

